title>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 193<br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/16/03 9:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=412.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Well</span><hr size=1> I may be over pessimistic and a bit bitter, but this thread is the perfect example of the way the skald situation has eveolved since this summer.<br>
<br>
The way 2h weapons work, interrupt formulas, the way damage add is calculated, what frontload damage mean, etc ... everything is pretty well known now, and, aside from bladeturn considerations, there is, on paper no debate. <br>
<br>
Like there has been no debate for the first 6 months of the game, where skalds were all powerful.<br>
<br>
Now, why do those kind of threads pop up ? Because skalds are less and less competent in the damage dealer role they played before, and are naturally trying to find other &quot;niches&quot;, other tactics, other ways to contribute besides beeing a speed bot. <br>
Your unspecced small shield, unfortunately, doesn't make you a defensive warrior, and you'll certainly not attack as fast as a dual wielding mercenary with your short sword, sorry.<br>
But, we aren't damage dealers anymore. So there HAS to be another way, right ? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dane@teamskald>Dane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 106<br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/19/03 3:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=412.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Some clarifications</span><hr size=1> NOTE: Faster weapons DO NOT PROC MORE.<br>
Procs are similar to DPS according to Mythic, it's procs per period of time.  So in truth, slow weapons proc more &quot;per hit&quot;, but the same over time.<br>
<br>
The nice thing about midgard is that you can swap between the two, 1H/S and 2H.  So more power to ya...anything to keep the game interesting for you.  If you had only ONE line to spec, I'd suggest 2H, since defense in RvR is VERY underutilized due to:<br>
<br>
1. Many classes won't even melee you.<br>
2. You are often hitting someone from behind or side, while someone else hits you from behind or side.<br>
3. Parry code still broken in group vs group RvR.<br>
4. Small shield not spec'd is really best boosted by a few levels of mastery of blocking...taking away from the potential of the 2H only spec.<br>
5. Haste has more potential benefit to 2H weapons due to haste cap.<br>
6. 2H damage cap (most notably when only hitting 1-2 times in RvR) is much higher...should check if it scales.  In my experience, I hit for about 600 with the 2H and about 200 with the 1H.  :/  3 hits later I catch up?  Thanks but no thanks.<br>
<br>
1H/S with mastery of block and high dex is &quot;possibly&quot; a better dueling/solo template.  But in RvR, if you can't block/stun/guard, you should be outputting damage...IF you are trying to optimize group RvR.  In the end, it's really whatever floats your boat.  I mean, some people pick blademasters when they would do far better to just come to mid and play a zerk ;0<br>
<br>
-Dane <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=412.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=412.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=412.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=412.topic&index=22><img src=http://www.stuckathome.com/skalded/images/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=412.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.threadControl?topicID=412.topic><img src=http://www.stuckathome.com/skalded/images/closethread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=412.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=412.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub36.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding